==English==

===Etymology===
[[in-]] + [[controvert]] + [[-ible]]

In- from [[Latin]] meaning ''not''
.Contro from Latin meaning to deny the truth of (something).
-ible from French -ible or Latin -ibilis.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/ˌɪŋ.kɒn.tɹəˈvɜː.təbl̩/}}
* {{audio|en|En-uk-incontrovertible.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Not capable of being [[denied]], [[challenged]], or [[disputed]]; closed to [[question]]ing.
#: {{ux|en|Her statement that Hitler was evil is '''incontrovertible'''.}}
#: {{syn|en|indisputable|undeniable|unquestionable}}
#: {{ant|en|controvertible}}

